From 9fe17ae1cab4eba519d9b5825bd504278e3a0bbf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Steve <steventhanhtuan@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 19:02:38 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 11/17] task4: wire the publication pass into the manager
 monitor loop

_run_publication_pass runs each tick after the migration cycle, guarded
by publication_gate+knowledge, single-island scope, and an mtime+count
signature so idle ticks cost one stat walk. The pass orchestrates
publication.py: harvest drafts per agent, verify and stamp shared
notes, group and rank once, regenerate each agent's views. Errors are
logged, never fatal to the loop.

Three review-found defects fixed along the way, each with a locked
regression test:
- the stored signature is the pre-pass one, so a mid-pass agent write
  is harvested next tick instead of being masked forever;
- harvest and view generation now share notes' user-note definition,
  and worktree seeding symlinks consolidate-owned housekeeping files
  (_connections.md, _open-questions.md, notes.md, raw/) so aggregates
  keep vanilla shared-write semantics instead of last-writer-wins;
- harvest records reconciled hashes into the manifest (persisted before
  the mirror), so a freshly stamped note settles after one follow-up
  tick instead of hot-looping the pass every tick.

700 passed, ruff clean.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
